<!-- HADITH DEBATE: corridor = the empty corridor of blind tradition -->

<section id="debate">
  <div class="wrap" style="padding-bottom:0">
    <div class="eyebrow rv">Qur&apos;anic Refutation</div>
    <h2 class="rv">15 Hadith Claims &mdash;<br><em>Answered</em> From the Qur&apos;an</h2>
    <p class="lead rv">From the research paper &ldquo;Qur&apos;anic Refutation of Hadith.&rdquo; These are the 15 most common arguments used to justify hadith authority &mdash; each refuted directly from the Qur&apos;anic text. Click any card to expand.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="wrap" style="padding-top:1rem">
    <div class="debate-layout">
      <div class="debate-sticky rv">
        <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="The corridor of blind tradition &mdash; leads nowhere" class="debate-img">
        <p class="debate-img-cap">The corridor of blind tradition. Millions walk it daily. The Qur&apos;an asks: where does it lead?</p>
        <div class="debate-qv">
          <p>&ldquo;Most of them follow nothing but assumption. And assumption can never replace the truth.&rdquo;</p>
          <cite>&mdash; Qur&apos;an 10:36</cite>
        </div>
        <div class="debate-qv" style="margin-top:0.8rem">
          <p>&ldquo;We did not leave anything out of the Book.&rdquo;</p>
          <cite>&mdash; Qur&apos;an 6:38</cite>
        </div>
        <div style="margin-top:1.5rem">
          <a href="https://lampofislam.wordpress.com/2022/03/15/criticism-of-hadith-from-a-quranic-viewpoint/" target="_blank" class="btn btn-outline" style="font-size:0.64rem;display:inline-block">Read Full Critique &rarr;</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="debate-cards rv d1">
        <div class="dc" onclick="this.classList.toggle('open')">
  <div class="dctop">
    <span class="dcnum">01</span>
    <div class="dccenter">
      <div class="dclabel">CLAIM</div>
      <div class="dcclaim">&ldquo;Obeying the Messenger means following Hadith&rdquo;</div>
    </div>
    <span class="dcplus">+</span>
  </div>
  <div class="dcbody">
    <div class="dcinner">
      <div class="dcrlabel">QUR&rsquo;ANIC REBUTTAL</div>
      <p class="dcrtext">Obedience to the Messenger means obeying the revelation he delivered. The Messenger is commanded to follow revelation alone (6:50), and his duty is to convey — not innovate external sources. Nowhere does the Qur'an equate 'obeying the Messenger' with books compiled two centuries after his death.</p>
      <div class="dcrverse">&mdash; Qur&rsquo;an 24:54 · 6:50</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="dc" onclick="this.classList.toggle('open')">
  <div class="dctop">
    <span class="dcnum">02</span>
    <div class="dccenter">
      <div class="dclabel">CLAIM</div>
      <div class="dcclaim">&ldquo;The Messenger was sent to explain the Qur'an&rdquo;</div>
    </div>
    <span class="dcplus">+</span>
  </div>
  <div class="dcbody">
    <div class="dcinner">
      <div class="dcrlabel">QUR&rsquo;ANIC REBUTTAL</div>
      <p class="dcrtext">The word in 16:44 is li-tubayyina — to make evident, not to add explanation from outside. The Qur'an clarifies itself (25:33). Its verses are 'perfected, then detailed from One who is Wise and Aware.' The Prophet highlights what is already revealed, not supplements it.</p>
      <div class="dcrverse">&mdash; Qur&rsquo;an 16:44 · 11:1 · 25:33</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="dc" onclick="this.classList.toggle('open')">
  <div class="dctop">
    <span class="dcnum">03</span>
    <div class="dccenter">
      <div class="dclabel">CLAIM</div>
      <div class="dcclaim">&ldquo;Hadith gives details of core practices like Salat&rdquo;</div>
    </div>
    <span class="dcplus">+</span>
  </div>
  <div class="dcbody">
    <div class="dcinner">
      <div class="dcrlabel">QUR&rsquo;ANIC REBUTTAL</div>
      <p class="dcrtext">The Qur'an defines each practice by purpose, ethics, and principle. Salat (root: ṣ-l-w) signifies connection and moral attentiveness — fully explained within the Qur'an alone. 'We did not leave anything out of the Book.' (6:38)</p>
      <div class="dcrverse">&mdash; Qur&rsquo;an 6:38 · 29:45 · 16:89</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="dc" onclick="this.classList.toggle('open')">
  <div class="dctop">
    <span class="dcnum">04</span>
    <div class="dccenter">
      <div class="dclabel">CLAIM</div>
      <div class="dcclaim">&ldquo;The Qur'an is too general; Hadith gives specifics&rdquo;</div>
    </div>
    <span class="dcplus">+</span>
  </div>
  <div class="dcbody">
    <div class="dcinner">
      <div class="dcrlabel">QUR&rsquo;ANIC REBUTTAL</div>
      <p class="dcrtext">The Qur'an calls itself mufaṣṣal (detailed) and tibyān (clarification of all things). 'Is it not sufficient for them that We have sent down the Book to you?' (29:51). To claim it is lacking contradicts God's own declaration.</p>
      <div class="dcrverse">&mdash; Qur&rsquo;an 29:51 · 41:3 · 6:114</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="dc" onclick="this.classList.toggle('open')">
  <div class="dctop">
    <span class="dcnum">05</span>
    <div class="dccenter">
      <div class="dclabel">CLAIM</div>
      <div class="dcclaim">&ldquo;Hadith is part of preserving the religion&rdquo;</div>
    </div>
    <span class="dcplus">+</span>
  </div>
  <div class="dcbody">
    <div class="dcinner">
      <div class="dcrlabel">QUR&rsquo;ANIC REBUTTAL</div>
      <p class="dcrtext">Only the Reminder (al-dhikr) — the Qur'an — is promised divine protection: 'Indeed, We have sent down the Reminder, and We will surely preserve it.' (15:9). There is no Qur'anic promise to preserve any other source.</p>
      <div class="dcrverse">&mdash; Qur&rsquo;an 15:9</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="dc" onclick="this.classList.toggle('open')">
  <div class="dctop">
    <span class="dcnum">06</span>
    <div class="dccenter">
      <div class="dclabel">CLAIM</div>
      <div class="dcclaim">&ldquo;The Messenger had legal authority beyond revelation&rdquo;</div>
    </div>
    <span class="dcplus">+</span>
  </div>
  <div class="dcbody">
    <div class="dcinner">
      <div class="dcrlabel">QUR&rsquo;ANIC REBUTTAL</div>
      <p class="dcrtext">The Prophet judged only by what was revealed: 'So judge between them by what God has sent down.' (5:48). 'I only follow what is revealed to me.' (6:50). His authority is inseparable from divine text.</p>
      <div class="dcrverse">&mdash; Qur&rsquo;an 4:65 · 6:50 · 5:48-49</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="dc" onclick="this.classList.toggle('open')">
  <div class="dctop">
    <span class="dcnum">07</span>
    <div class="dccenter">
      <div class="dclabel">CLAIM</div>
      <div class="dcclaim">&ldquo;Companions followed Hadith; we must too&rdquo;</div>
    </div>
    <span class="dcplus">+</span>
  </div>
  <div class="dcbody">
    <div class="dcinner">
      <div class="dcrlabel">QUR&rsquo;ANIC REBUTTAL</div>
      <p class="dcrtext">'They followed their forefathers, even if they understood nothing.' (2:170). 'If you obey most of those on Earth, they will mislead you from God's path.' (6:116). Truth is not determined by majority or historical precedent.</p>
      <div class="dcrverse">&mdash; Qur&rsquo;an 2:170 · 6:116</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="dc" onclick="this.classList.toggle('open')">
  <div class="dctop">
    <span class="dcnum">08</span>
    <div class="dccenter">
      <div class="dclabel">CLAIM</div>
      <div class="dcclaim">&ldquo;Rejecting Hadith is rejecting the Prophet&rdquo;</div>
    </div>
    <span class="dcplus">+</span>
  </div>
  <div class="dcbody">
    <div class="dcinner">
      <div class="dcrlabel">QUR&rsquo;ANIC REBUTTAL</div>
      <p class="dcrtext">The Prophet's role is limited to conveying: 'The Messenger's duty is only to convey clearly.' (5:99). Accepting his mission means accepting the Qur'an he conveyed — not hearsay reports compiled 200 years after his death. Verse 59:7 refers to war spoils, not a blank authority for Hadith.</p>
      <div class="dcrverse">&mdash; Qur&rsquo;an 5:99 · 59:7</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="dc" onclick="this.classList.toggle('open')">
  <div class="dctop">
    <span class="dcnum">09</span>
    <div class="dccenter">
      <div class="dclabel">CLAIM</div>
      <div class="dcclaim">&ldquo;Isnād science ensures Hadith authenticity&rdquo;</div>
    </div>
    <span class="dcplus">+</span>
  </div>
  <div class="dcbody">
    <div class="dcinner">
      <div class="dcrlabel">QUR&rsquo;ANIC REBUTTAL</div>
      <p class="dcrtext">Historical chains of narrators are still human conjecture, not divine preservation. 'They only follow conjecture, and conjecture is no substitute for truth.' (53:28). 'Do not follow what you have no knowledge of.' (17:36).</p>
      <div class="dcrverse">&mdash; Qur&rsquo;an 17:36 · 53:28</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="dc" onclick="this.classList.toggle('open')">
  <div class="dctop">
    <span class="dcnum">10</span>
    <div class="dccenter">
      <div class="dclabel">CLAIM</div>
      <div class="dcclaim">&ldquo;Hadith fills in Qur'anic gaps&rdquo;</div>
    </div>
    <span class="dcplus">+</span>
  </div>
  <div class="dcbody">
